name: ABC
text:
WATCH LIVE: ABC News has continuing coverage as the country awaits results from several key states in the 2020 presidential election.

https://t.co/pk0wUBiEIl

name: ABC
text: Demonstrators marched through the heart of Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, demanding that all votes cast in the election be counted—as the state continues to tally early, mail-in ballots. https://t.co/k6GQgIK3FP https://t.co/sVjLOCFm64

name: ABC
text: .@jonkarl says Trump’s strategy “seems to be to basically create doubt about the integrity of the election itself, which seems to be reflection that he believes that if all the counting goes on to conclusion, he will not emerge in the lead.” https://t.co/6oJ9txzJZ1 #Election2020 https://t.co/SY7dMZbcgy

name: ABC
text:
.@TomLlamasABC gives an update on the path to 270 and the different paths to victory for Pres. Trump and Joe Biden. 
#Election2020
https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 https://t.co/I2LLuJHy9p

name: ABC
text: Cruise Lines International Association announced today that its members would maintain the ongoing voluntary suspension of cruise operations in the U.S. through Dec. 31, 2020. https://t.co/HwXvevv1mo

name: ABC
text: TONIGHT AT 10PM ET: @GStephanopoulos anchors a primetime special on @ABCNetwork and @ABCNewsLive as #Election2020 continues. https://t.co/Mjub2wzWpH https://t.co/HyFVeMGRqT

name: ABC
text: “It is mathematically possible” for Joe Biden to close the gap and win the state of Georgia, “though the math and the vote generally favors the president here,” ABC News’ @SteveOsunsami reports. https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 #2020Election https://t.co/dsxaUS8uGq

name: ABC
text: .@matthewjdowd on the state of #Election2020: “We’re as divided as we were since 1860...Abraham Lincoln won that election in 1860 with 40% of the vote.” https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 #Election2020 https://t.co/YEQEkB8rtk

name: ABC
text:
Voters in Mississippi approved the design of a new state flag, which will include an image of a magnolia, the state flower, and the phrase "In God We Trust."

The previous state flag featured the Confederate Battle Cross. https://t.co/4APQcacpJM

name: ABC
text: NEW: As votes are being counted, the Trump campaign filed a lawsuit in Georgia on Wednesday night — its third of the day. https://t.co/DDJAqVnyni #Election2020

name: ABC
text:
Firefighters in Honduras helped save several people, including an infant, from flooding caused by Tropical Storm Eta.

Although Eta has weakened to a tropical depression, it continues to bring life-threatening flooding to parts of Central America. https://t.co/IAO1tLMcYK https://t.co/jDxNLn2e3P

name: ABC
text: NEW: Incumbent Democratic Sen. Gary Peters wins Michigan Senate race, @ABC News projects. https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 #Election2020 https://t.co/StM4La0kth

name: ABC
text: GOP Rep. Adam Kinzinger on Trump's ballot claims: “If there is a legitimate concern and you have evidence of that, there’s an entire court system…set up to handle that. But it is not by making accusations through Twitter that have a reverberating impact” https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 https://t.co/sB3vRQNvW0

name: ABC
text: RT @FiveThirtyEight: Republican women are faring quite well in the House and Senate races we’ve been watching. https://t.co/WbrOED1TZs

name: ABC
text: Voters in this election paved new paths for LGBTQ+ candidates, who made historic firsts across all levels of American government. https://t.co/D6R6OOcuUp

name: ABC
text: LATEST: The Trump campaign has filed a second lawsuit in Pennsylvania. https://t.co/m0gIpdvXKS #Election2020

name: ABC
text: RT @ABCPolitics: .@WhitJohnson gives an update on the state of the race in AZ; Maricopa County released the results of 76K ballots but still has 338K to count and will release an update later tonight. https://t.co/DA8JdVxU42 #Election2020 https://t.co/kqnqiN3IfW

name: ABC
text:
ELECTION LATEST: https://t.co/DsbRBKQI5N

- Biden team launches transition website.
- Trump campaign files multiple lawsuits.
- PA governor says he'll "fight like hell" to continue counting votes.
- Nevada not expecting new results today.

name: ABC
text: .@devindwyer says Biden campaign “not worried at all” about legal threats because there isn't a convincing "constitutional argument put forward in any court by the Trump campaign that would challenge the legitimacy of any of the results in a real way.” https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 https://t.co/Z2Kg8qStp3

name: ABC
text: When will we get results in unprojected states? The @FiveThirtyEight team breaks it down: https://t.co/iF6BOwVsJG #Election2020
